    • Method Detail

      • addToKey

        final boolean addToKey(java.lang.String word,
                       java.lang.String eWord)
        Checks to make sure that a pair (one encrypted and one decrypted word) are compatible with the current version of the key. If they are, then that pair is added to the key. Instances where a match is not valid: 1. No letter can decrypt to itself 2. If the encrypted letter already exists but matches to a different decrypted letter 3. If the decrypted letter already exists but matches to a different encrypted letter
        Parameters:
        word - encrypted word to be added to key
        eWord - decrypted word to be added to key
        Returns:
        true if pair is compatible, false if it's not

      • updateKey

        final Index updateKey(main.com.cryptogram.solver.stackStuff.Stack<Index> stack,
                      java.util.List<java.lang.String> words)
        This method updates the Key when a word gets removed from the Stack Algorithm: 1. Pop one Index off the Stack 2. Re-input all other pairs still on the Stack to ensure that no older word had the same key/value pair
        Parameters:
        stack - the current Stack of words that have been solved
        words - List of all the encrypted words
        Returns:
        the Index that got popped off the Stack
